## Topic
Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP)

## What I Learned
- DHCP automatically assigns network settings to devices.
- The DORA process consists of Discover, Offer, Request, and Acknowledge.
- Devices use DHCP to obtain an IP address automatically.
- Broadcast messages are used when a device does not yet know the DHCP server.
- I captured DHCP Request and DHCP ACK packets in Wireshark.

## Tools Used
- Kali Linux
- Wireshark

## Key Observation
My Wireshark capture showed a DHCP Request from a device using source IP 0.0.0.0 and a DHCP ACK from the DHCP server confirming the IP assignment. This likely represented a DHCP lease renewal.
